their advantages.

77
00:04:44,466 --> 00:04:46,066
-Cut it out, will you?

78
00:04:46,166 --> 00:04:47,933
-You won't let me
speak with him then?

79
00:04:48,033 --> 00:04:49,166
-Huh?

80
00:04:49,266 --> 00:04:51,266
-I'm sorry, but I'm not
sure it's such a good idea.

81
00:04:51,366 --> 00:04:55,000
-But I-- Ranma, dear,
I need to talk to you.

82
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:57,233
-Hey, why'd she
just call you dear?

83
00:04:57,333 --> 00:04:58,633
-Jeez, what are
you asking me for?

84
00:04:58,733 --> 00:04:59,266
-P-- please!

85
00:04:59,366 --> 00:05:00,166
Wait!

86
00:05:00,266 --> 00:05:01,966
Ranma's in the dark about this.

87
00:05:02,066 --> 00:05:05,266
It'll be better if I can
break it to him in my own way.

88
00:05:05,366 --> 00:05:06,433
-I'll only take a minute.

89
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:07,633
Please, you've got to--

90
00:05:07,733 --> 00:05:08,700
-I'll let you talk to him.

91
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,733
OK?

92
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:11,633
Just let me soften
him up a bit first.

93
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:12,466
-Dear!

94
00:05:12,566 --> 00:05:13,933
GENMA: Oh, for crying out loud.

95
00:05:15,233 --> 00:05:17,466
Ranma, I gotta go
out for a while.

96
00:05:17,566 --> 00:05:18,766
I'll explain when I get back.

97
00:05:20,133 --> 00:05:21,033
WOMAN: Ranma, dear!

98
00:05:21,133 --> 00:05:22,833
-So what was that all about?

99
00:05:22,933 --> 00:05:25,000
Whatever it was, he
is up to no good.

100
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:26,733
HAPPOSAI: His past has
caught up with him.

101
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:31,566
Of course, Genma was but
a mere youth at the time.

102
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:36,433
As I've told you many
another time, the three of us

103
00:05:36,533 --> 00:05:39,166
walked the earth in order
to polish our skill.

104
00:05:51,366 --> 00:05:54,066
As it so happened,
Genma fell in love.

105
00:05:54,166 --> 00:05:57,300
The name of the young maiden was
Sakura, as in cherry blossom.

106
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,166
Nature took it's
course, and in due time

107
00:06:01,266 --> 00:06:03,000
the beautiful
Sakura was delivered

108
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:06,033
of a healthy baby
boy whose name was--

109
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:07,400
-Wait, you don't have to say.

110
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,866
It was Ranma, wasn't it?

111
00:06:08,966 --> 00:06:09,966
-Huh?

112
00:06:10,066 --> 00:06:12,400
-Fate, however, had
not finished with it.

113
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:17,100
The girl's parents
opposed match and decided

114
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,933
that they should be separated.

115
00:06:19,033 --> 00:06:21,700
Genma and the baby
went back on the road

116
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:25,300
while Sakura stayed
behind, forever by herself.

117
00:06:28,066 --> 00:06:30,766
Their union was
reckless and impulsive.

118
00:06:30,866 --> 00:06:34,166
However, I cannot find it
in my heart to blame them.

119
00:06:34,266 --> 00:06:36,466
-Odd how I've never
heard that story before.

120
00:06:36,566 --> 00:06:38,366
-Yeah, you know, I'm
surprised that Pop never

121
00:06:38,466 --> 00:06:40,033
said nothing about it.

122
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:41,933
-Oh Ranma, it's it obvious?

123
00:06:42,033 --> 00:06:44,433
I'm sure he just wanted
to spare you the misery.

124
00:06:45,533 --> 00:06:46,800
-Well, jeez.

125
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:48,433
I mean, if he was going to go
to all the trouble of being

126
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:51,466
a single father, at least he
got to sow the wild oats first,

127
00:06:51,566 --> 00:06:52,166
right?

128
00:06:52,266 --> 00:06:52,900
Don't you agree Akane?

129
00:06:54,466 --> 00:06:55,766
-Be quiet.

130
00:06:55,866 --> 00:06:59,033
-In other words, she has come
to reclaim her long lost son.

131
00:06:59,133 --> 00:07:02,266
-No wonder she was so
desperate to see Ranma again.

132
00:07:02,366 --> 00:07:04,933
-How could she remarry
after something like that?

133
00:07:05,033 --> 00:07:07,400
Imagine being alone
all these years.

134
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:10,166
-We've got to do
something to help her.

135
00:07:10,266 --> 00:07:11,533
-I agree.

136
00:07:11,633 --> 00:07:14,500
Somehow we've got to bring those
three together as a family.

137
00:07:18,066 --> 00:07:18,833
-You can count on me.

138
00:07:18,933 --> 00:07:20,100
-On me too, son.

139
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,233
-On my too.

140
