I can't breathe.

189
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:06,466
-But Ranma, why do you
need me when you've got

190
00:09:06,566 --> 00:09:09,233
those three cute fiances.

191
00:09:09,333 --> 00:09:11,133
TATEWAKI (VOICEOVER):
Now wait a second.

192
00:09:11,233 --> 00:09:12,933
If he's going to
be leaving anyway,

193
00:09:13,033 --> 00:09:15,300
why don't we let him go?

194
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:19,700
Once the current Saotome
is out of the picture,

195
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:25,033
Akane Tendo will become
mine-- physically, mentally,

196
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:25,574
inevitably.

197
00:09:30,533 --> 00:09:31,533
-He must be set free!

198
00:09:31,633 --> 00:09:33,100
-He must be kept here!

199
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:33,866
-Give him liberty!

200
00:09:33,966 --> 00:09:35,066
-Or give death.

201
00:09:35,166 --> 00:09:36,100
It don't matter because--

202
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,400
-It works either way.

203
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:39,000
All for one, and one for all.

204
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:40,266
-We guys gotta stick together.

205
00:09:41,466 --> 00:09:43,233
-Will you please
quiet before I hit you

206
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:44,933
upside the head with my spatula?

207
00:09:45,033 --> 00:09:46,300
-Let's solve this
democratically.

208
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:51,166
All those in favor of
Ranma taking a hike,

209
00:09:51,266 --> 00:09:52,366
raise your hands.

210
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:55,933
Sorry girls, the majority rules.

211
00:09:56,033 --> 00:09:57,800
-Oh, give us a break.

212
00:09:59,766 --> 00:10:00,800
-What a bunch of losers.

213
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:02,566
How are you gonna beat
me when you can't even

214
00:10:02,666 --> 00:10:03,466
beat a bunch of girls?

215
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:05,700
-Ranma, darling?

216
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:06,300
-Ranma, honey!

217
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:07,266
-Ranma!

218
00:10:07,366 --> 00:10:08,933
HAPPOSAI: Stop right there.

219
00:10:09,033 --> 00:10:10,466
-Grandfather Happosai?

220
00:10:10,566 --> 00:10:11,900
-Listen here, girls.

221
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,633
Helping to choose a
future daughter-in-law

222
00:10:13,733 --> 00:10:16,566
is the sacred duty of
all Japanese mothers.

223
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:19,166
Don't tell me you're trying
to take that privilege away

224
00:10:19,266 --> 00:10:20,266
from her.

225
00:10:20,366 --> 00:10:22,700
-Do you really think
she'd choose one of us?

226
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,900
-I'd say that's
entirely up to you

227
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:28,900
and how willing you are to be
an obedient daughter-in-law.

228
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,800
-I will be the most dutiful
daughter who ever lived.

229
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:34,600
-I'll set a world
record for humility.

230
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:36,500
-Shampoo make Ranma proud.

231
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,300
HAPPOSAI: Listen
carefully, girls.

232
00:10:40,966 --> 00:10:44,900
In order to better your chances,
the role of Ranma's mother

233
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,033
will be played by yours truly.

234
00:10:47,133 --> 00:10:47,700
To work!

235
00:10:49,533 --> 00:10:50,766
Oh my, my.

236
00:10:50,866 --> 00:10:52,333
Would you look at that?

237
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:54,600
Girls these days, I tell you.

238
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:57,066
Nothing wrong with them a
good switching wouldn't cure.

239
00:10:58,633 --> 00:11:02,300
[panting]

240
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,300
Chop chop, girls.

241
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:06,000
The floor isn't going
to clean itself.

242
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:08,433
[panting]

243
00:11:08,533 --> 00:11:09,066
Over here.

244
00:11:09,166 --> 00:11:11,466
You missed a spot.

245
00:11:11,566 --> 00:11:12,633
What about over here?

246
00:11:15,433 --> 00:11:17,933
And what are you
doing here, my child?

247
00:11:18,033 --> 00:11:19,133
-What do you think?

248
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:20,433
-Well, bless your heart, dear.

249
00:11:20,533 --> 00:11:21,933
And the very best
of luck to you.

250
00:11:23,233 --> 00:11:24,100
Why aren't you working?

251
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,133
-I'm done.

252
00:11:25,233 --> 00:11:26,200
-What, already?

253
00:11:26,300 --> 00:11:27,866
You can't have done
a very thorough job.

254
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:32,400
Oh yes, well what
about this, then?

255
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:35,233
What's this I see?

256
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:38,500
You're not disrespecting
me, are you?

257
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:41,500
I'd simply hate to pull
you from the competition.

